  "text": "To discriminate T RM cells from T EM cells, more phenotypic markers are needed. In human skin, 50%-70% of T cells express CD69 and CD103 [CITATION_1] . Although CD69 has been characterized as a T-cell activation marker, it has been shown to be constitutively expressed by a subset of T cells within peripheral tissues under steady-state conditions [CITATION_2] (Figure 1 ).",
